                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.00/2327.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Clare</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Bluefields</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 9, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your telegram July 7. Sands badly wounded and was brought to this Consulate about
                    1 a.m., 6th; consent given to keep him at the Consulate a few days; delivered to
                    the authorities yesterday and sent hospital.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Clare</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
